simulation instances, significant variability exists in the timing of decline, with some populations persisting until approximately step 2000 while others reach near-extinction by step 500. Despite this variation in persistence time, all trajectories converge on zero, suggesting that under the specified parameter configuration—including 20 hunters, processing costs of 3-6 energy units, and life history constraints such as 730-tick birth spacing and senescence at 7300 steps—the hunting pressure consistently overwhelms the population's reproductive capacity and demographic resilience." 																							
